===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|bere}}, from {{inh|en|ang|bēor|t=beer}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*beuʀ}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*beuzą|t=beer}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*bʰews-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*bews-|t=dross, sediment, brewer's yeast}}.

Cognate with {{cog|stq|Bjoor||beer}}, {{cog|fy|bier||beer}}, {{cog|nds-de|Beer||beer}}, {{cog|nl|bier||beer}}, {{cog|de|Bier||beer}}, {{cog|is|bjór||beer}}, {{cog|sv|buska||freshly brewed beer, new beer}}, {{cog|dum|-}} & {{cog|gml|-}} {{m|dum|bûsen|t=to feast, booze, drink heavily}}, {{cog|gmh|būs||a swelling}}. Non-Germanic cognates include probably {{cog|sq|mbush||to fill, stuff}}.

